16. cxb5
17. gxf6 {17.Qxb5+?this intermediate check fails to17...Nfd7!and Black remains a piece up.} 
17. Nc4 {We are relying on very concrete play now.17...Qc6?unfortunately runs into18.d5!Nxd519.Bxd5Qxd520.Bc3!and with a nice discovered attack on the queen and pawn on g7 Black can't avoid the loss of material.} 
18. d5 {18.fxg7?Bxg7only helps Black activate the forces. Note that d4-d5 is no longer possible as b2 is hanging.} 
18. a4
