11. Bd5 {The knight on h4 is stranded, as the move f2-f3 prevents it from returning to the center. Specifically, if, for example, the bishop moves somewhere and ...g7-g5 is played, the knight would be trapped. Therefore, it is advisable for White to consider trading off the light-squared bishops on d5.12.Bxd5Nxd513.Qd2, preventing Black from pushing the pawn to g5.13...Nc6!White's bishop on c3 appears unfavorable, and on the next move, Black is likely to castle queenside, ensuring the safety of the king while exerting significant pressure on White's pawn on d4 with the rook on d8 and other pieces.} 
