17. Kb2 {If White makes a critical error with17.h5?Black seizes the opportunity and plays17...Qxa3!to capture a pawn with a double attack, hitting the bishop on a2. White responds with18.Kb1, seemingly maintaining control. But Black surprises with18...b5!It's an impressive move, as Black prepares ...Nc4. It should be noted that White cannot capture on b5, as it would allow Black to win the queen by bringing the rook to the b-file.  Black continues the attack with19.hxg6Nc4!, threatening mate on b2. Black follows up with20.Bxc4bxc4, followed by a rook check on b8. At this point, White can only avoid immediate resignation by sacrificing a significant amount of material.} 
