12. dxe6
12. Bxe6
13. Bxe6
13. Qxe6
14. Re1
14. Qf5 {Keeping an eye on c-pawn and therefore making it harder for White to become active.} 
15. Nh4 {The only real challenge, chasing the queen away.} 
15. Qd5 {We have to trust that the endgame is holdable for Black.} 
16. Qxd5
16. Nxd5
17. Rad1
17. N7b6 {The best construction for Black under these particular circumstances. Since the white rooks have already been placed on the open files Black should at least retain control over the entry squares d7 and e7.17...Nxc3?18.Rxd7and White will start collecting pawns.} 
