21. Ne7+
21. Nxe7
22. Bxb6 {22.Rxe7??is a huge blunder, in view of22...Rd823.c3c5and Black even wins.} 
22. cxb6 {The other recapture is also fine, but opening the c-file for counterplay is even more accurate.} 
23. Rxe7
23. Rc8 {Very precise!23...Rd8?!24.g3Rd225.Rc7!±leads to an unpleasant rook endgame.} 
24. c3
24. Rd8
25. g3
25. Rd2 {As mentioned, with the pawn on c2, White could still torture the opponent with Rc7.} 
26. Rxb7 {26.b4Ra227.Rxb7Rxa3=} 
26. Rxb2
27. Rxa7
27. Rc2 {White can't stick to the extra pawn.} 
28. Rc7
28. Ra2 {White can’t stick to the extra pawn. All pawns on the queenside are going to be traded, resulting in a 3 vs. 3 on the kingside.} 
