8. Qe2 {White has the idea of castling queenside and is prepared to capture on c6 in case Black chooses to castle, after which the queen can swing over to a6.} 
8. e6 {Postponing castling and preparing the dark-squared bishop to be released.} 
9. O-O-O
9. Bd6 {Black finds themselves in a satisfactory position. It is worth noting that in this scenario, Black will likely opt to castle kingside. Once White plays h2-h3, posing a question to the bishop on g4, Black can respond by capturing on f3, leading to isolated and doubled pawns on the f-file. This particular line, with the opening of the g-file, carries the potential for sharper dynamics compared to the alternative move 7...Nbd7. Nevertheless, both options appear viable for Black.} 
