7. Ncxe2 {Positionally speaking an interesting choice, as White realizes the knight is badly placed on c4 and given the chance, White would like to expand on the queenside later on.   Not surprisingly strong players like Karpov and Adams played it as well. With this recapture, White violates the general principles of opening play and the knight even hinders the development of some of White's other pieces.} 
