12. dxc5
12. Bxc5+
13. Kh1 {Of course, White doesn´t capture on c5 as that loses the bishop on c4. After this move, White is about to install the bishop on c3 with enormous pressure against the knight on f6.} 
13. Nxe4
14. fxe4
14. O-O
15. Nf4
15. Nc6
16. Nh5
16. Bd4 {was seen in the game Naiditsch-Stevic, Bol 2013, when White could have obtained now a very dangerous initiative, starting with} 
17. Ra3 {when pretty soon almost all White's pieces will be directed against the black king.} 
