11. Be3
11. Na6 {A small refinement upon earlier games in which Black decided to castle immediately.} 
12. Ne4
12. Nxe4
13. fxe4
13. Qc6 {The point of Black's play, as Black attacks both the bishop on c4 as well as the pawn on e4.In case of14.Qd3there is14...Nb4!} 
14. Bb3
14. Qxe4 {The principled move, otherwise White retains both the bishop pair and a wonderful pawn centre.} 
15. Qd2
15. Nb4 {White has some compensation for the pawn, but I would be confident here as Black. The knight rejoins play as it controls the d5-square and soon the black king can be brought into safety.} 
