12. Qxd5
12. Be6
13. Qe4 {When Black is in huge trouble already.} 
13. Qb4+ {This doesn't really win a piece.} 
14. Nc3
14. Qxc4
15. Qxb7 {White picks up the rook on a8. In any case, this line shows once again Black has to be very precise carrying out the pawn break ...c7-c5 at the right moment.} 
