9. Ne5 {With the idea of taking the bishop on c4 followed by the pawn on d5.} 
10. Qf5+
10. Ned7 {Black is advised to use this knight to block the check, as now ...e7-e6 a serious threat.} 
11. Qf3 {The only move, making it harder for Black to develop the remaining piece on the kingside.11.Bd2?an attempt at ignoring Black's idea, but White actually ends up in serious trouble.11...e6!exploiting the pin along the fifth rank.12.Qg5exd513.Nxd5the main point of White's move 11.Bd2. It looks as if White is doing fine, but the tactics are not over yet!13...Qc5!Keeping the momentum by attacking the bishop on c4.14.Nxf6(14.Bb3?there is no time to consolidate the position with a move like this14...Re8+check!15.Be3Qa5+one more check!16.c3Re5-+double attack, winning the knight on d5).14...Qxc4the right capture, as White is unable to get the king out of the centre.15.Nxd7Rxd7-+and Black is quickly developing a devastating attack.} 
11. Ne5 {And a repetition of moves seems to be the logical outcome of the game.The alternative11...Nb612.Bb3Nbxd5does win a pawn, but after13.Bd2=∞White's bishops are offering reasonable compensation.} 
