13. c3 {I have tried to make this line playable for Black, but frankly, I am not satisfied with the results of my discoveries. After:} 
13. Qxb2
14. Nf4
14. Qb5 {14...e5Black would like to undouble the e-pawns, but15.Nd3!15...Qb516.Nfxe5Nxe517.Nxe5±favors White.} 
15. Qe2
15. Qxe2+
16. Kxe2
16. Nd8
17. Nxd8
17. Rxd8
18. Rhe1
18. Rd6
19. Kd3
19. Kd7 {Black would love to play ...g7-g5.} 
20. Kc2 {Followed by20...--21.Nd3White retains a pleasant risk-free edge.} 
