4. Nf6 {Basically the only square for the knight. Depending on White's next move, Black will bring the light-squared bishop into the game (either to f5 or g4) before putting the pawn on e6.} 
5. a3 {An uncommon move, although it has been seen in a few games, including those by some grandmasters. White's intention is to potentially displace the queen with b2-b4.Nonetheless, I would recommend approaching it similarly to how we handle lines with5.Bd2and5.Bc4.} 
