10. O-O
10. O-O {Black finds themselves in a playable position, similar to the lines that arise after 5.Bd2. White may have a slight advantage due to their increased space, but this also comes with added responsibility. However, I believe that Black has decent chances in this position. There are two possible plans to consider:   1) Playing ...a7-a5 to counter White's b5-b4 with ...a5-a4, creating a square for the queen on a5. Additionally, ...c7-c6 may be a future consideration.  2) Another option is ...a7-a6, intending to exchange our light-squared bishop on b5 to create more space for our remaining pieces.} 
