11. Ne3 {A clever intermediate move. If White takes on e3 Black can safely take on e5 with a good game.} 
12. Nc6 {White would like to take on e3, but first gives away the knight under favorable conditions  (weakening Black's queenside).} 
12. Qxc3 {A spectacular move, but unfortunately it doesn't offer more than equality. White can't take the queen at the end of the line the knight on c6 is still hanging.} 
13. Bxe3 {After other moves White remains a piece down.} 
13. Qxb2
14. Nxa7 {Material equality.} 
14. Bf5 {With a more or less equal middlegame.} 
