[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4
1. d5
2. exd5
2. Qxd5
3. Nc3
3. Qa5
4. g3 {The idea of fianchettoing the bishop is not very common against the Scandinavian, still it has been played by some very strong grandmasters. White attempts to exert pressure on the long diagonal and particular against the pawn on b7.} 
4. Nf6 {Like in the main lines covered in earlier chapter I'd like to start with this developing move.} 
5. Bg2 {The big question is how Black is going to arrange the queenside development.} 
5. e5 {White has refrained from occupying the centre with the d-pawn and therefore I believe it makes a lot of sense to take the opportunity grabbing space in the centre. Black doesn't mind an early contact of the two remaining central pawns. White has now to decide how to develop the knight from g1.} 
6. Nf3 {White intends to increase the pressure against the pawn on e5.} 
6. Bd6 {The ideal square for the bishop, supporting the pawn on e5.} 
7. O-O
7. O-O
8. Re1 {An useful inclusion.} 
8. Re8 {Likewise, as the rook overportects the pawn on e5 one more time.} 
9. d4
9. Bg4 {Putting pressure on the knight and indirectly the pawn on d4, but the main threat is to win a piece by means of...e5-e4.} 
10. h3
10. Bxf3
11. Bxf3 {Threatening to take on b7 and keeping the rook on e1 protected with the queen.11.Qxf3now the rook on e1 is temporarily unprotected11...Nbd7!Black connects the rooks and is doing pretty fine, as soon ...c7-c6 will be played. White is unable to take on b7 as the pawn on d4 is hanging at the moment.} 
11. Nc6 {Attacking the pawn on d4. White could now take on c6, doubling pawns on the c-file, but then the most important defender of the king won't be there any longer.} 
12. d5
12. Nd4 {The main idea behind Black's strategy. The knight is wonderfully placed in the centre.} 
13. Bg2
13. Bb4 {With a strategically sharp battle ahead, in view of the imbalances in pawn structure and bishop vs. knight. Perhaps White is a tad better, but Black's position doesn't contain any weaknesses and I think there are quite some good practical chances thanks to the knight on d4.} 
