12. Bg2 {White is looking for a discovered attack on the queen.} 
12. g6 {12...Bc4?tactically fails to13.Ne5!!Qxg2(13...Bxd314.Nxc6followed by Rxb7 clearly favors White).14.Qxc4offers White a decisive attack.} 
13. O-O {Doesn't work for White.} 
13. Bc4 {A skewer.} 
14. Ne5 {Otherwise Black just wins the exchange.} 
14. Qxg2+ {The refutation, as this check comes with check!} 
15. Kxg2
15. Bxd3
16. Nxd3
16. O-O-O {Attacking the pawn on d4.} 
17. Ne5 {Going after the pawn on f7.} 
17. Rxd4
