7. O-O-O {Following our standard plan of bringing the king into safety and activating the rook to the half-open d-file.} 
8. c3
8. Qg6 {Eyeing the d3-square when White's queenside will be paralyzed.} 
9. d4 {Otherwise White's last move 8.c3 would definitely make no sense.} 
9. e5 {with excellent piece play for Black in Bozic-Cabarkapa, Kragujevac 2013.} 
10. d5
10. Nf6 {Simple developing move and preparing ...e5-e4 so that White's bishop no longer defends the pawn on d5.} 
