6. c4 {Frankly, the main point of refraining from an early Nc3 is to be able to play this move and gain more influence in the centre.} 
6. Qf5 {The best square for the queen, keeping the d-file free for the rook on d8, while White isn't able to keep harassing the queen. With the last move, Black is intending to take on f3 after which the pawn on d4 is hanging.} 
7. Be3 {The main move. By developing the bishop to e3 White believes the pawn on d4 to be well supported. However, for unprepared players Black's next two moves may come as a huge shock!} 
7. Bxf3 {The most straightforward approach as Black is planning to win the pawn on d4.Alternatives like7...e5and7...Nf6are playable but aren't ensuring Black full equality.} 
8. Bxf3
