9. Bxd4
9. Qe6+ {Since White was still threatening to win the queen by means of ...Bg4, this check is the only way to justify our previous move.Note that10.Kf1?runs into Qxc4 and thanks to the double attack Black regains the piece remaining two pawns up.} 
10. Be2 {The only move, as blocking the check with the queen would leave the bishop on d4 undefended.} 
10. c5 {Another way to regain the piece, is also good enough for equality with precise play. Frankly, this may be an even more practical option for Black.However, I believe that with10...Qe4!?there are also better practical chances to play for more than equality if White is not up to the task.} 
