3. exd3 {No fear, just take the pawn!} 
4. Bxd3
4. Nc6 {In my opinion, the most accurate solution, as Black retains the option of challenging the bishop on d3 with either ...Nb4 or ...Ne5.} 
5. Qe2 {A novelty. White avoids the exchange of queens along the d-file.} 
5. Nd4 {Taking advantage of the misplacement of the queen on e2.} 
6. Qe5
