7. Bf4
7. Ne6
8. O-O-O {A tricky idea, as8...Nxf4?runs into9.Bb5winning the queen.8.Qb5+?!discovered check on the queen, but Black has8...Qd7∓and now either the queens and/or bishop on f4 or getting exchanged.} 
8. Qxe5
9. Bxe5
9. c6 {Always preventing the knight from leaping to either d5 or b5.} 
10. Nf3
10. Nf6
11. Rhe1 {White has optimized its pieces but is still a pawn down.} 
11. Nc5 {The key move to untangle. Black is preparing to capture the bishop on d3 and develop its own bishop to g4, followed by ...e7-e6. White's compensation for the pawn is insufficient.} 
